    <TaskName>Basal Metabolic Rate</TaskName>
    <TaskDescription>
        &lt;strong&gt;Goal: &lt;/strong&gt;Read the information given by your instructor. Construct a model NEWLINE
        for a 20 year old man who weighs 180 pounds, is 71 inches tall, and is NEWLINE
        moderately active (HB Factor = 1.55). Show his weight change if he NEWLINE
        consumes 500 less calories than he burns each day. After constructing NEWLINE
        the model click "Show Graph" or "Show Table" to enter your own values. NEWLINE
        Then complete the worksheet. NEWLINE NEWLINE
        
        &lt;strong&gt;BMR Formulas &lt;/strong&gt;(weight is in pounds, height in inches, age in years): NEWLINE        
        Women: BMR = 655 + (4.35 x weight) + (4.7 x height) - (4.7 x age) NEWLINE
        Men: BMR = 66 + (6.23 x weight) + (12.7 x height) - (6.8 x age) NEWLINE NEWLINE
        
        &lt;strong&gt;Harris Benedict Formulas: &lt;/strong&gt; NEWLINE
        Sedentary (little or no exercise): BMR x 1.2 NEWLINE
        Lightly active (light exercise/sports 1-3 days/week): BMR x 1.375 NEWLINE
        Moderately active (moderate exercise/sports 3-5 days/week): BMR x 1.55 NEWLINE
        Very active (hard exercise/sports 6-7 days a week): BMR x 1.725 NEWLINE
        Extra active (very hard exercise/sports): BMR x 1.9 NEWLINE NEWLINE        
    </TaskDescription>
